        <abstract>
            <p>Has tried using dealers’ price-lists as a guide to sex ratios in Lepidoptera; finds numerous cases in which the sexes bring different prices and in virtually all of them the males are cheaper. This seems to confirm the impression of the field collectors.</p>
            <p>Wishes RT good luck with natural history in S. Africa.</p>
        </abstract>
